title: -Gamma-Ray Production Cross Sections for Fast Neutron Interactions With Al, Ni, Cu and Nb.

x4codes.shortRef: Conf: Conf.on Nucl.Cross Sections F.Techn.,Knoxville 1979, p.45 (1979)

Prog: Japanese report to NEANDC, No.61, p.112 (1979)

x4freetext: -GAMMA-RAY PRODUCTION CROSS SECTIONS FOR FAST NEUTRON
INTERACTIONS WITH AL, NI, CU AND NB.
DEUTERIUM GAS TARGET BOMBARDED BY PULSED
.NATURAL MIXTURES OF HIGH PURITY METAL (OVER 99 PC),
AS A HOLLOW CYLINDER 2 CM INNER DIAM., AND 4 CM
OUTER DIAM. FOR AL, NI AND CU. FOR NB, A RIGHT
CYLINDER OF 2CM BY 3CM LONG WAS USED.
EACH SAMPLE WAS PLACED AT THE CROSSING POINT OF THE
DEUTERON BEAM AXE AND THE GAMMA-RAY DETECTOR AXIS.
THE SAMPLES WERE AT 10.5 CM FROM THE TARGET.
TIME OF FLIGHT USED TO DISCRIMINATE AGAINST
THE PULSES FROM SCATTERED NEUTRONS AND OTHER TIME
2 INCH BY 2 INCH NE-213 LIQUID SCINTILLATOR
AT 613 CM FROM THE TARGET WAS USED TO MONITOR THE
NEUTRON FLUX. DETECTION EFFICIENCY WAS OBTAINED BY
70 CM3 DETECTOR PLACED AT 165 CM FROM THE
SAMPLE USED TO MEASURE THE GAMMA-RAYS. THE RESOLUTION
WAS ABOUT 5 KEV FOR 1.33 MEV GAMMA RAYS FROM A CO-60
SOURCE. THE DETECTOR WAS HEAVILY SHIELDED.
.THE FERDOR CODE WAS MODIFIED AND USED TO RESOLVE THE
GAMMA RAY SPECTRA  AND OBTAIN TOTAL GAMMA RAY
IN THE UNFOLDING PROCEDURE USED, CLEAR PEAK COMPONENT
WERE SUBTRACTED FROM THE RAW SPECTRA TO AVOID THE
UNDESIRED VIBRATION. THEN, THE SPECTRA WERE SMOOTHED
AND BUNCHED INTO 100 KEV ENERGY BINS, AND THE
UNRESOLVED GAMMA RAY PRODUCTION CROSS SECTIONS WERE
OBTAINED BY UNFOLDING THE DATA. TOTAL GAMMA RAY
PRODUCTION CROSS SECTIONS WERE CALCULATED BY ADDING
THESE UNRESOLVED AND RESOLVED GAMMA RAY PRODUCTION
THE ERROR DUE TO THE UNFOLDING PROCEDURE IS ESTIMATED
AT 10 TO 30 PERCENT INCLUDING THE UNCERTAINTIES OF
A.P.T. JAPAN CODE CHANGED TO JPN
.CORRECTIONS HAVE BEEN MADE FOR ATTENUATION AND
MULTIPLE SCATTERING EFFECTS AND FOR THE ATTENUATION
OF PRODUCED GAMMA-RAYS IN THE SAMPLE.
CORRECT. FOR THE ATTENU. OF GAMMA RAYS IN THE
ENERGY PEAKS- 5 PERCENT FOR E LESS THAN 3.5 MEV,
.COUNTING STATS OF THE PEAK AREA AND THE CONTINUUM
COMPONENT UNDER THE PEAK- 1 TO 40 PERCENT.
